## Overview

The integration tests verify end-to-end workflows and complete user interactions across the Discovery Hub application. Unlike unit tests that test individual components in isolation, integration tests ensure that multiple components work correctly together as a unified system.

## What Are Integration Tests?

Integration tests:
- Test complete user workflows from start to finish
- Verify interactions between different components (models, views, URLs, templates)
- Check that redirects work correctly based on user state
- Validate permission and access control across sections
- Test filter functionality and data flow through multiple layers
- Ensure data persistence and retrieval work end-to-end

